2. Dlotaea: Dicte is a mountain in the eastern part of Crete. The Phoenicians, in very ancient times, were colonists and traders among the Grecian islands. Several ol the divinities worshipped by the Greeks were probably introduced by them. The fable ol Europa may perhaps point to such a settlement in Crete, with the introduction of cattle srom Asia. The heller which guides Cadmus would thus have the same signification in thestory with the bull which bears away Europa.
